A production-ready Node.js + TypeScript project.

## What you need to modify

Your project has 7 files. You only need to care about 2:

| File | What it does | When to edit |
|------|-------------|-------------|
| `src/index.ts` | Your application logic | **Every time** |
| `tests/index.test.ts` | Tests for your code | **Every time** |
| Others (eslint config, tsconfig, AGENTS.md) | Project infrastructure | Almost never |

## Quick Start

```bash
npm install
npm run dev
```

The server starts at **http://localhost:3000** with a JSON health endpoint.

## Scripts

| Command | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| `npm run dev` | Dev mode with tsx hot-reload |
| `npm run build` | Compile TypeScript to `dist/` |
| `npm start` | Run compiled production code |
| `npm test` | Run tests (Vitest) |
| `npm run test:watch` | Watch mode |

## Project Structure

```
src/
├── index.ts          # HTTP health server, graceful shutdown
tests/
├── index.test.ts     # Integration tests against real server
```

## Stack

- **Runtime**: Node.js 22+ (ESM, `"type": "module"`)
- **Language**: TypeScript 5.8 strict mode
- **Testing**: Vitest 3.x (integration tests with node:http)
- **Dev runner**: tsx (TypeScript execution with watch)
